      <h2>To Begin - Launching Point</h2>
      <h3>Visual Syllabus</h3>
      <p>A course requires a course outline. When we all taught in class these
        details were printed out. And shared and read in class. The course
        outline was important. It contained important information about
        policies, assignments and other key details</p>
      <p>But now, with many part of a course online. The course website seems to
        be replacing the syllabus. But there is still a need to offer a take
        away summary or birds eye view, Cue the <a href="images/media/admin_visual.png"
          title="Visual Syllabus" target="_blank">visual syllabus</a>. Its an
        infographic for your course</p>
